        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 12:57PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 1257 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wideman, or 10 miles northwest of Melbourne, moving east at 65 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Heart...                          Franklin...
Zion...                           Agnos...
Violet Hill...                    Kittle...
Union...                          Larkin...
Saddle...                         Ballard...
Cherokee Village...               Ash Flat...
Horseshoe Bend...                 Calico Rock...
Wideman...                        Gorby...
Oxford...                         Center...
Morriston...                      Glencoe...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
